European Stocks Are Little Changed, U.S. Futures Rise; Commerzbank Climbs

-- B y   W i l l   H a d f i e l d
-- 
2011-04-06T08:03:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/european-stocks-are-little-changed-u-s-futures-rise-commerzbank-climbs.html
European stocks retreated after
Federal Reserve minutes showed U.S. policy makers are divided
over whether to maintain record stimulus past June. Asian shares
fell and U.S. index futures gained.  Deutsche Bank AG fell 2.4 percent after a report that
 Germany ’s biggest bank will seek shareholder approval to raise
as much as 18 billion euros ($25.7 billion) in fresh capital.
Commerzbank AG rose 1.8 percent as it said it will sell equity
worth as much as 11 billion euros to repay government aid.  The Stoxx Europe 600 Index slid 0.3 percent to 280.07 at
9:01 a.m. in  London . Even so, the benchmark measure has advanced
6.8 percent from this year’s low on March 16 as investors
speculated that the economic recovery will withstand
 Japan ’s worst earthquake on record and popular revolts in the
Middle East and north Africa.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Hadfield at 
 whadfield@bloomberg.net  